## Identity & Scope
- This is the chemsmart project â€” an open-source computational chemistry planning & HPC automation toolkit.
- The primary codebase is Python (3.10+), with tools for Gaussian and ORCA job generation, submission, and analysis.
- Scope is strictly: computational chemistry workflows, HPC operations (queues, jobs, logs, schedulers), plus the agent/TUI layer.
- chemsmart supports local (v13.1 model + MLX 4-bit on Apple Silicon) and cloud (OpenAI/Anthropic) agent providers.

## Python Code Style
- Target Python 3.10. Use type hints for function parameters and return values.
- Follow PEP 8. Max line length: 79.
- Use f-strings for string formatting.
- Use context managers (`with` statements) for resource management.
- Write docstrings for all public classes and functions.
- Prefer composition over inheritance.
- Formatting: `black` (line-length=79), `isort` (profile=black).
- Linting: `ruff` (target-version=py310, line-length=79), `flake8` (ignore E226, W503, W504).
- Before pushing, run: `make fmt`, `make lint`, `make test`.
- Do NOT print shell installation commands (`pip install`, `apt install`, `brew install`, etc.) in code or docs. Refer to README/docs instead.

## Commit Conventions
- Use conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.
- Link issue numbers in commit messages when applicable.
- Write clear commit messages that explain WHY, not just WHAT.
- Pre-commit hooks run `make fmt` â†’ `make lint` â†’ `make clean` â†’ `make docs-lint` â†’ `make docs-fmt` â†’ `make docs-clean` automatically.

## Testing Discipline
- Run `make test` before pushing. All tests must pass.
- Test framework: `pytest` with `pytest-mock`, `pytest-cov`, coverage (branch=True).
- Aim for 100% code coverage. Write tests for all new functionality.
- Test paths: `tests/`. Agent-specific tests in `tests/agent/`.
- Mark slow tests with `@pytest.mark.slow`.
- Test markers: `slow`, `agent`, `integration`.
- Run with: `pytest --strict-markers --disable-warnings`.

## Project Architecture
- CLI entry point: `chemsmart = "chemsmart.cli.main:main"` (Click-based).
- Agent layer: `chemsmart/agent/` â€” prompts (`prompts/*.md`), local adapter (`local/`), TUI (`tui/`), registry, session management.
- System prompt assembly: `chemsmart/agent/prompts/identity.py` â†’ `build_system_prompt()`.
- Local model: `Smilesjs/chemsmart-qwen2.5-coder-3b-instruct-v13_1` emits compact SPEC JSON; deterministic postprocessor + adapter renders real CLI commands.
- Agent config: `~/.chemsmart/agent/agent.yaml` or `agent.v13_1.yaml.example`.
- MLX path (Apple Silicon): `mlx_loader.py` with `mlx-lm==0.31.3`.
- Package data includes: `agent/prompts/*.md`, `agent/local/*.md`, `agent/local/*.yaml.example`, `agent/tui/*.tcss`.

## Agent & Prompt Development Rules
- Planner prompt (`planner.md`): returns JSON with `steps`, `rationale`, `estimated_cost`, `intent` (workflow|advisory|chitchat).
- Tool kinds are canonical and exhaustive: `gaussian.sp|opt|ts|freq|irc|scan|modred|nci|resp|tddft|dias|crest|traj|wbi|qmmm|qrc`, `orca.sp|opt|ts|freq|irc|scan|modred|neb|qmmm|qrc`.
- Taskâ†’kind mapping is strict: TS = `*.ts` (never `*.opt`), IRC = `*.irc` (never `*.opt`), SP = `*.sp` (never `*.opt`).
- Critic prompt (`critic.md`): returns verdict (ok|warn|reject), confidence (0.0â€“1.0), issues, rationale. Be conservative â€” prefer warn over ok when unsure.
- Tool loop (`tool_loop.md`): use registered tools only when materially helpful. Preview/validate before risky actions.
- Compact planner (`planner_compact.md`): output-only JSON SPEC; never emit runtime-owned fields (project, functional, basis, solvent, etc.).
- Step references use 1-based indexing: `"$step1"`, `"$stepN.field"`.

## Chemistry Domain Guardrails (Critic Rules)
- Reject kind-task mismatches (TSâ†’opt, IRCâ†’opt, SPâ†’opt, opt+freq as standalone freq step).
- Warn on: TS/IRC on small symmetric molecules without reaction context, minimal basis for production, IRC without prior freq-confirmed TS, open-shell without unrestricted method, anions without diffuse basis.
- `geometry handoff missing`: warn when SP step uses raw `build_molecule` instead of `extract_optimized_geometry` result.
- `dry_submit=true`: do NOT warn about missing server/queue/account/scratch/module fields.

## Key Dependencies
- Core: `ase`, `pymatgen`, `rdkit`, `numpy~=1.26.4`, `scipy`, `click`, `pyyaml`, `pydantic>=2`, `rich`, `tenacity`.
- Agent cloud: `openai>=1`, `anthropic>=0.40`, `python-dotenv>=1`.
- Agent local: `transformers==4.56.2`, `accelerate==1.10.0`, `huggingface_hub>=0.34.0`.
- Agent MLX: `mlx-lm==0.31.3` (requires separate env; transformers>=5, huggingface_hub>=1.5).
- Agent TUI: `textual>=0.80`, `watchdog>=3`, `pyperclip`.
- Dev: `black==26.1.0`, `isort==7.0.0`, `ruff`, `pre-commit>=3.6.0`.
